.SH NAME
bb-pr-status - Show pull request status for a repository


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr status [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Show pull request status for one repository, including the current branch pull request when available, open pull requests created by you, and open pull requests requesting your review.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for status

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--limit\fP=50
	Maximum number of open pull requests to inspect for status

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr status
  bb pr status --repo workspace-slug/repo-slug
  bb pr status --json current_branch,created,review_requested
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbb-pr(1)\fP


